attributes.descriptionHtml:
Helloooooooo!! My name is Smoke. My foster mom likes to make up songs about me, and sometimes she calls me Smokey, Smokey Bones and Smokestack.

Life for me hasn't always been great.....

My last person kept me chained on a very short chain in the kitchen or crated, unless they wanted to use me for a stud dog. Then, they stopped feeding me. I don't really know don't know why they did that to me.
One day a lady calling herself a Guardian came and took me on a car ride. My owner told the Guardian that the neighbor had poisoned me, so they took me to the doctor. I was so happy to break free from those chains. Truth is, I just needed food, and love.
The next day, I met my foster mom. Although she loves me very much, she tells me that I can't stay with her forever. She promised me that she would love me until my new person finds me.   I have never really had the opportunity to be a puppy, so now.....I am making up for lost time.
I love my foster kids, but I I'm going to need some time and patience so a home with older kids would be best. My biggest downfall is that I just get too excited and want to jump. I loved my foster brothers though (3yrs & 11yrs) and am very protective.

I need a patient person/family that can give me lots of exercise and is willing to set boundaries and continue to work on my manners. Im a big boy and I like to go full speed.   I am not really a fan of smaller animals, like cats. They look like toys, but they don't like when I play with them. I like some other medium to large easy going dogs but would require a slow introduction.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Louie's adoption donation is $300 has been neutered, microchipped, received his rabies, distemper/parvo, bordetella and flu vaccinations, tested negative for heartworms and has started on prevention, as well as flea protection. He also has had a dental cleaning.

Louie was surrendered to a shelter for unknown reasons. Upon rescuing him, it was discovered he had a heart murmur. After a consultation with a cardiologist, Louie was diagnosed with several heart defects. Surgery was being considered until he was then diagnosed with a possible liver shunt. It was then decided to not do surgery. Louie's life expectancy is really unknown but with known medical issues he has been stable with us and has done very well.  He had been with a foster home but unfortunately she could no longer care for him.  Since he has been stable with regular monitoring, we are making available for adoption.

Louie has personality plus! He is a "talker" and is so enthusiastic about life! Squeaky toys are his favorite. Louie  is also a little love bug and loves to cuddle with his people. He will snuggle right under your chin so he can lay his head on your heart. Louie is a "typical " miniature poodle as he can be protective. Louie loves food and has no problem trying to take food from any other dog so he is best to feed by himself. A home with older children is preferred. . 

Louie does very well on house training if kept on a schedule. He likes to be outside but he is not a long walker as he tires easily. This little guy gets along with other dogs, but does do better with females than he does males. Louie is just adorable and anyone would fall in love with this lil guy.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi furiends! I'm Mango and my partner in crime, Mia.

Here's a little about us. Our first owner died suddenly and we were left all alone. Then we were rescued and went to a very nice Foster family, where our Foster Mom treated us like her very own babies. And then one day,  we met and were adopted by a nice family. We lived with them for about a year. Due to unforeseen circumstances they had to bring us back to DASH  We are staring to age so we would love our very own human(s) we can Love, Snuggle and Cuddle with and take long naps together. We like to follow you wherever you go but we won't disturb your peace and quiet, as we promise we rarely ever bark. Not to mention, we don't mind being crated when you're away, or take us with you, we love going for car rides. We potty outside as long as we are taken outside frequently. We still enjoy going for short walks.

Our top 3 favorite things in life are food, big cozy beds, and sunshine! We don't like the cold weather, snow, or rain! I must share with you, that we can't hear very well. We use to follow our (first)Foster Mom's hand signals instead of her voice. And I (Mango) had to have my right eye removed after I was rescued due to a bad infection. But it doesn't phase me. Mia doesn't like to be picked up but she always needs help to get up on the couch. We get along well with other doggies and kids who don't topple all over us. I'm not sure whether we like cats or not, we haven't had any kitty friends before. But we're so laid back, sweet, and affectionate. We're really easy pups to care for but we will need daily brushing and will need to see a groomer every month or every other month to keep us nice and handsome and pretty.

We can't wait to finally have a FOREVER family!!

www.dashanimalrescue.org
Dashrescue00@gmail.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Bobo’s adoption donation is $375 and he is being fostered in Northeast Ohio.  He has been neutered, microchipped, received his rabies, distemper/parvo, bivalent canine influenza, and Bordetella vaccines, tested negative for heartworms and started on heartworm/flea/tick prevention. He has also had a dental cleaning.  Bobo requires a home with a strong veterinary history.

Bobo was surrendered by his previous owner when he didn't get along with another dog in the home and the owner stated that he was aggressive toward another dog in the home who was first aggressive towards him. Thankfully, someone advocated for him and his foster mom has not seen evidence of aggression. He most likely will thrive in a home with no young children under the age of 10 years old and with a dog that is of calmer temperament. His forever pawrents must also be comfortable with his growls because he is a talkative dog - albeit all bark and no bite. He just likes to "trash talk" He favors men and possibly older women. His foster mum says, "He's so funny because he seems to not like me too much because he growls at me the most. He'll come and growl when I put ear drops or his belly band but won't walk away from me and will instead lean in for scratchies. He's very loving, sweet and a really good cuddler. He's hefty so he's extra nice to cuddle with. He's got these beautiful, soulful eyes that seem to speak to you and everyone in the house loves him so so much."  Bobo is on a special diet due to allergies and must remain on that diet. Bobo has done really well with housetraining on a schedule. He enjoys car rides and walks with his foster bros.

He hasn't been trained much on a leash but he loves to go for walks to sniff. He knows to sit and his name, but he would like his new family to teach him more tricks as long as they provide yummy treats. Qtip is potty trained and crate trained and will bark at you if he needs to use the potty. 

Qtip would be great in an only pup home or a home with other dogs. Once he learns the dog dynamic he adjusts pretty easily to any home situation. Qtip is such a sweet, loving, happy dog and is ready for his forever family to love him for the rest of his life!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Delani’s adoption donation is $475 and she is being fostered in Central Ohio.  She has been spayed, microchipped, received her rabies, distemper/parvo, bivalent canine influenza, and bordetella vaccines, tested negative for heartworms and started on heartworm/flea/tick prevention. Delani requires a secure, physically fenced yard.

Delani came into rescue as a breeder release from a commercial puppy mill and has made incredible progress in rescue.  She is still skittish and learning to walk on a leash (so the fenced yard requirement is a must have) but she is an incredibly happy, happy, happy girl who becomes attached to her people fairly quickly.  Delani is an active girl and would be best in a home where someone is home a fair amount to continue her progress moving forward.  She does well with children but we believe that a home with children over the age of 8 would be best because she is rambunctious and very playful.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Dogs posted are currently up for adoption unless otherwise noted.  Our goal is to match dogs with a suitable home/family so that at any time, dogs shown here may already have a potential match.  We post dogs as quickly as possible however there may be some not yet pictured. We allow our dogs time to settle in with their foster families so that we can evaluate their health and personality.   Sparky is 3 yrs old and   a Collie Aussie mix who has attributes of both breeds.  He is friendly, cuddly, smart and curious.  He enjoys toys but likes humans even more.  He is excited to meet any human that crosses his path and wants to know where his family of humans is, preferring to be near them. 

 

He plays exuberantly with his foster doggie siblings and would probably enjoy being the only dog or else with a dog who is active and non-dominant.  He is working on commands and walking politely on a leash.  He is crate trained and sleeps and eats in his crate as he did at his former owner’s home.  He rides well in the car with a bit of help to get in but he might bark at large trucks or motorcycles.  His energy and attentiveness we believe would make him a prime candidate for agility training and he would love being part of an active family. He is very interested in squirrels and rabbits so needs to be leashed or have a fenced in yard.  He has not been around cats or children.  He would do best with  a savvy dog owner who is going to capitalize on his strengths and he in turn will be your faithful, eager companion.

 The adoption fee for Dixie is $250.00

attributes.name: Colony Cats (& dogs)
attributes.adoptionProcess: We have an application that requires the potential adopter to wait 24 hours until their application can be verified. Once everything checks out the adopter comes and picks up their new fur member of the family and signs a contract. One of the highlights of our contract states that if for ANY reason at ANY time they cannot care for the animal, they must return the cat or dog back to Colony Cats (& dogs). Our adoption fees are $75.- for kittens (6 months and younger), $65.- for cats, $45.- for Wise Whiskers (7 years and older). We often have adoption specials where the adoption fees are lowered. The adoption fee includes the animals already being spayed/neutered, Feline Leukemia tested (cats), Heartworm tested (cats and dogs), all vaccinations (FVRCP and DHLPP), rabies vaccine (if kittens or puppies adopted are not old enough to have received a rabies vaccine, then the new owner can bring them back for that at no extra cost), microchip, flea/tick/heartworm preventative.
attributes.about: We are a 501c3, non-profit, all volunteer animal rescue and welfare organization. We are dedicated to ending the explosion of homeless pets in this area; through low cost (sometimes no cost) spay/neuter, public education/awareness, rescue/adoption and support for feral/stray cats and their caregivers. We do this because there is an epidemic of abused, neglected, abandoned animals throughout Central Ohio. As a compassionate organization we are striving to end this suffering for them. Get them medical care, food and if necessary, a new home.
attributes.services: Rescue/Adopt, Spay/Neuter and Support for feral/stray cats and their caregivers

attributes.name: Ohio Fuzzy Pawz Shih Tzu Rescue, Inc.
attributes.adoptionProcess: Applicant submits an online (or paper) application.  We thoroughly check references including personal, vet, and groomer--landlord if applicable.  Once references check out, we then conduct a home visit to ensure home and family would best suit the dog.  We do not adopt on a first come, first served basis--we go with the home that is the best fit for the dog.
attributes.about: We rescue, rehabilitate and re-home Shih Tzu and other toy breed dogs from a variety of situations.  We pull from a number of shelters in and around Ohio; we take in breeder releases from commercial breeding facilities and owner surrenders as space permits.  We do this so that hopefully we can reduce the number of Shih Tzu and other breeds euthanized in shelters due to space and place all of our dogs in loving permanent homes.
